description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Considering a career in District Nursing? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESHT are excited to announce that we have an opportunity for Band 5 registered nurses to join our District Nursing Service in Eastbourne:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are you interested in working in the community?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you want to be part of an innovative team that is remodelling its adult community nursing services to ensure they are fit for the future?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you fancy a change?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you have a passion for 1:1 patient care?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are you keen to advance your management skills in long term conditions?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you want to be part of team that is fast-paced and varied?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you recognise your need to extend your knowledge and skills?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will join a team that:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aims to change patients’ lives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aims to fully engage patients in their self-care and outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A fantastic opportunity for your own professional development!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;There are opportunities to undertake specialist education and competencies so that you will be able to lead and case manage complex patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will have monthly clinical supervision to support you and enhance your clinical practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will have the opportunity to work within a multidisciplinary team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will have the opportunity to complete the District Nurse Specialist Practitioner Pathway&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Excited at this possibility? Want to know more?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join a dynamic and highly skilled team in delivering skilled care to the patients of East Sussex living in Eastbourne and surrounding areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit nurses who have good time management skills and can work well under pressure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is designed to enable the successful applicants to maintain:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Core clinical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mandatory Training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend safety huddles and team meetings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in collaboration with other teams to enable seamless working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The skills that can be developed as part of this role include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Catheter management, including trouble shooting with leaking and blocked catheters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Palliative Care &amp; End of Life Care - supporting patients and families with Last days of Life care giving stat doses of medications and setting up syringe drivers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administering intravenous antibiotics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wound care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administration of medications e.g. Insulin, Clexane, GCSF&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holistic Assessment Skill&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;East Sussex Health Care are committed to providing a high-quality, safe and sustainable service which is fit for the future and able to reflect changing patient needs within our local community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Service reconfiguration and additional investment has enabled&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The development of new roles with extended skills and scope of practice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Development of a seven-day service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhanced career progression opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Community care in East Sussex is now based around Primary Care Network (PCN) teams. These provide integrated multi-disciplinary services, supporting individualised patient care and the needs of the local population&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bev Walding Operational Manager for Seaford, ALPS and Central Primary Care Networks&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address b.walding@nhs.net Telephone number 07920 244519&lt;/p&gt;
